cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new deep learning method for this task, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions multi-task learning, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the use of identity labels, which could suggest it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a new benchmark for intra-camera supervised person re-identification, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
